{"version":"NotebookV1","origId":1083584440950372,"name":"6-2 Dataset API","language":"scala","commands":[{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950373,"guid":"6b3d1494-6a37-43f2-9712-bc494be7b7c9","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":1.0,"command":"\n%md\n# Datasets: The DataFrame Query Language vs. Lambdas\n\nThe Dataset API gives you the option to use both the DataFrame query language _and_ RDD-like lambda transformations.","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"a65db1e2-fb5f-413e-a95a-eb4940fe1f93"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950374,"guid":"32266f64-c427-493a-886f-6a66d2d73275","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":2.0,"command":"case class Person(id: Integer, firstName: String, middleName: String, lastName: String, gender: String, birthDate: String, ssn: String, salary: String)\n\nval personDS = spark\n  .read\n  .option(\"header\", \"true\")\n  .option(\"inferSchema\", \"true\")\n  .option(\"delimiter\", \":\")\n  .csv(\"dbfs:/databricks-datasets/learning-spark-v2/people/people-with-header-10m.txt\")\n  .as[Person]\n\npersonDS.cache().count","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"95cd3d54-3f34-4bd8-9855-7d66d8170a71"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950375,"guid":"3e461227-2263-4f2b-afcf-42888e2db753","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":3.0,"command":"// DataFrame query DSL\nprintln(personDS.filter($\"firstName\" === \"Nell\").distinct().count)","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"7995e5bc-9d62-4dff-9086-4b760b7972b0"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950376,"guid":"3c04e57a-36c9-4ee2-a355-dfc25529669c","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":4.0,"command":"// Dataset, with a lambda\nprintln(personDS.filter(x => x.firstName == \"Nell\").distinct().count)","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"6affd3f0-f421-421e-bbdd-a5c9e235d81d"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950377,"guid":"d0a94808-e93e-45bf-96eb-8404ada0a96f","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":5.0,"command":"%md\n\n### Tungsten Encoders' effect on Catalyst Optimization\n\nThe Domain Specific Language (DSL) used by DataFrames and DataSets allows for data manipulation without having to deserialize that data from the Tungsten format. \n\n<img src=\"https://files.training.databricks.com/images/tuning/dsl-lambda.png\" alt=\"Lambda serialization overhead\"/><br/>\n\nThe advantage of this is that we avoid any *serialization / deserialization* overhead. <br/>\nDatasets give users the ability to carry out data manipulation through lambdas which can be very powerful, especially with semi-structured data. The **downside** of lambda is that they can't directly work with the Tungsten format, thus deserialization is required adding an overhead to the process.\n\nAvoiding frequent jumps between DSL and closures would mean that the *serialization / deserialization* to and from Tungsten format would be reduced, leading to a performance gain.","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"7b5f2baa-8018-44b1-928f-151b2e86a1fe"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950378,"guid":"9a67a830-ed82-469d-832a-b648a3f46c32","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":6.0,"command":"%md-sandbox\n\n- Advantages of using lambdas:\n    - Good for semi-structured data\n    - Very powerful\n- Disadvantages:\n    - Catalyst can't interpret lambdas until runtime. \n    - Lambdas are opaque to Catalyst. Since it doesn't know what a lambda is doing, it can't move it elsewhere in the processing.\n    - Jumping between lambdas and the DataFrame query API can hurt performance.\n    - Working with lambdas means that we need to `deserialize` from Tungsten's format to an object and then reserialize back to Tungsten format when the lambda is done.\n    \nIf you _have_ to use lambdas, chaining them together can help.","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"49938396-720d-4ad8-9f9d-e24a96800846"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950379,"guid":"de493a3b-50ee-4962-bd20-433cd1b6a524","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":7.0,"command":"// define the year 40 years ago for the below query\nimport java.util.Calendar\n\nval earliestYear = Calendar.getInstance.get(Calendar.YEAR) - 40\n\npersonDS\n  .filter(x => x.birthDate.split(\"-\")(0).toInt > earliestYear) // everyone above 40\n  .filter($\"salary\" > 80000) // everyone earning more than 80K\n  .filter(x => x.lastName.startsWith(\"J\")) // last name starts with J\n  .filter($\"firstName\".startsWith(\"D\")) // first name starts with D\n  .count()","commandVersion":1,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"3f5b59c1-7614-4b18-84a4-ae2917c636b3"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950380,"guid":"439c0218-949a-41c9-b25e-0928a052143e","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":8.0,"command":"import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._\n\npersonDS\n  .filter(year($\"birthDate\") > earliestYear) // everyone above 40\n  .filter($\"salary\" > 80000) // everyone earning more than 80K\n  .filter($\"lastName\".startsWith(\"J\")) // last name starts with J\n  .filter($\"firstName\".startsWith(\"D\")) // first name starts with D\n  .count()","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"f9b2f258-7c22-4b55-8fd8-884e045ad58a"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950381,"guid":"cf2fe708-4d82-4a22-bce6-629163fef0e5","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":9.0,"command":"%md\nLook at how much faster it is to use the DataFrame API!\n","commandVersion":0,"state":"finished","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible